The paper proposes a machine learning model based on neural networks for correcting molecules in discrete representations using a structure rule learned from a collection of undirected molecular graphs. The paper focuses on the application of natural language processing techniques to molecular graphs, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of language modeling, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques for processing molecular graphs (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the use of discrete representations of molecules, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.SD (Scientific Computing).
